laboratory_examinations.findings: Elevated liver enzymes including ALT, AST, ALP, and LDH; mild hyperkalemia; high lactate; blood pH of 7.20 (normal value is 7.35-7.45).
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: On the fourth day in the ICU, no anemia and elevated hepatic enzymes were noted. On discharge, ALT was at 285 U/L and AST at 65 U/L (normal values: ≤ 35 U/L for ALT and ≤ 35 U/L for AST).

laboratory_examinations.findings: Mature placenta with microcalcifications, intervillous hemorrhage, vascular congestion, and edema.
